reviews.review: Loved it. I don't get the reviews and think some people just want to hate Star Wars. But to each their own...and this one was definitely one for me.

It felt 3Â½ hours long as it plodded along predictable paths, accompanied by extensive exposition to ensure enlightened understanding, since the story-telling was so inept. 

Make no mistake, the movie was gorgeous. The special effects were as good as I've ever seen. But if Lucasfilm/Disney does another, I suggest spending more effort on the writing, and less on the eye-candy. 

As an aside to Rotten Tomatoes, if you're going to provide falsified audience scores, I suggest you vary them a bit up and down around your preselected number as the total rises. It would make it more believable.

Only good in the sense that TLJ set a really low bar. It's a rushed through attempt to try and salvage what TFA started. 

In comparison to the rest of the franchise the action is dumb, the characters flat, and story emotionless. One of those things were "just give me a synopsis" would be an adequate alternative to sitting through it.

I have watched it twice. The first time I wasn't sure if I liked it. The second time I saw it I freaking loved it. I didn't like that Rose wasn't seen being the spokesperson for the Everyman in the StarWars universe. I feel like Rey's story had to be what it was, and I wish I could see more of Ben Solo. Adam Driver acted his butt off, and I loved it.

Fantastic! Ignore the critics...if you love Star Wars, you'll love this finale. No movie is perfect - but JJ and crew did the near impossible by crafting an inspiring, exciting, beautiful final episode to a 40 year journey. Loved and can't wait to watch it again!
I think it wrapped up the last Jedi stuff quick which does make the film seem rushed, but once last that I found the film great and just as dark as I hoped it would be. Worth every penny.

i stood in line for 3 hours to see the very first STAR WARS movie, and this is a fitting end to this saga!...I enjoyed every single moment...i recommend this finale of a saga that has been with all of us since the 70's!!
Movie was so much fun and excitement. Great trilogy ending for a Star Wars fan. Fire the critics -  can't believe they gave it such bad reviews.
Aloe start to the movie. Was losing me than the ending shined
I loved the movie. Great story, great cinematography, the perfect way to end a Saga!
